When using a TagFilter to include/exclude a tag that represents a JUnit 4 category, e.g. `com.acme.Foo`, the Vintage Engine correctly returns a filtered tree of `TestDescriptors` after discovery. However, when executing these `TestDescriptors`, Vintage will run all test methods in a class that contains an included test method.

For example, given the following test class

```java
public class ExampleTests {
    @Test
    @Category(Foo.class)
    public void foo() {}

    @Test
    public void bar() {}
}    
```

and an `includeTags("com.acme.Foo")` filter, Vintage executes both `foo` and `bar`. Similarly, for an `excludeTags("com.acme.Foo")` filter, Vintage runs both methods.

